? (cond
    .(condition value)
    .(condition value)
    ...)

For each argument (clause), if .condition is true, return .value. Otherwise,
test the next clause...
Return false if no condition was true.

Example:
  (use 'io' 'flow')
  (fput (stdout)
        (cond
          .((no)  'not printed\n')
          .((yes) 'printed\n')
          .((yes) 'not printed\n')))
  # prints 'printed'
